      • retrieveAllRequests

        @GetMapping(path="/requests")
public java.util.List<Request> retrieveAllRequests()
        Display all the requests available on the endpoint
        Returns:
        a list of all the requests in JSON format using the method findAll() from the class RequestDaoService
        See Also:
        http://localhost:8080/requests displays the requests

        @GetMapping annotation maps HTTP GET requests onto specific handler methods. It is a composed annotation that acts as a shortcut for @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.GET).

      • retrieveRequest

        @GetMapping(path="/requests/{id}")
public Request retrieveRequest(@PathVariable
                                                                   java.lang.String id)
        Display all the requests available on the endpoint

        @GetMapping annotation maps HTTP GET requests onto specific handler methods. It is a composed annotation that acts as a shortcut for @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.GET).

        @PathVariable annotation handles dynamic URIs where one or more of the URI value works as a parameter.

        Parameters:
        id - the identification number of the request.
        Returns:
        a specific request in JSON format using the method findOne() from the class RequestDaoService.
        Throws:
        RequestNotFoundException - if the request is null.

      • createRequest

        @PostMapping(path="/requests")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<java.lang.Object> createRequest(@RequestBody
                                                                                                               Request request)
        Push a new 'Request' object on the server.

        @PostMapping annotation is specialized version of @RequestMapping annotation that acts as a shortcut for @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.POST). @PostMapping annotated methods handle the HTTP POST requests matched with given URI expression.

        @RequestBody annotation indicating a method parameter should be bound to the body of the web request.

        The location of the object (i.e. using @GetMapping(path="/requests/{id}") is correlated to the obj_id of the request (see below) 
         URI location = ServletUriComponentsBuilder
                 .fromCurrentRequest()
                 .path("/{id}")
                 .buildAndExpand(savedRequest.getDocId()).toUri();
        Parameters:
        request - represents the object Request.
        Returns:
        a ResponseEntity, e.g. represents the whole HTTP response: status code, headers, and body. The method builds the object (JSON format) at a given location.

      • retrieveAllACTICOResponses

        @GetMapping(path="/responses")
public java.util.List<Output> retrieveAllACTICOResponses()
        Display all the responses from ACTICO Server. Responses are gathered in JSON format following past requests.
        The method retrieves findAllResponses from RequestDaoService.

        @GetMapping annotation maps HTTP GET requests onto specific handler methods.
        It is a composed annotation that acts as a shortcut for @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.GET).

        Returns:
        a list of all the answers in JSON format using the method findAllResponses() from the class RequestDaoService. The results are in the shape of 'Output' objects.
        See Also:
        http://localhost:8080/requestsACTICO displays the requests

      • retrieveResponse

        @GetMapping(path="/responses/{id}")
public Output retrieveResponse(@PathVariable
                                                                    java.lang.String id)
        Display a specific response from ACTICO server.

        @GetMapping annotation maps HTTP GET requests onto specific handler methods.
        It is a composed annotation that acts as a shortcut for @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.GET). @PathVariable annotation handles dynamic URIs where one or more of the URI value works as a parameter.

        Parameters:
        id - the identification number of the request.
        Returns:
        a specific request in JSON format using the method findOneResponse(id) from the class RequestDaoService
        Throws:
        RequestNotFoundException - if the output (i.e. response) from ACTICO is null.

      • removeResponse

        @DeleteMapping(path="/responses/{id}")
 @ResponseBody
public void removeResponse(@PathVariable
                                                                                   java.lang.String id)
        Delete an output (i.e. the response from ACTICO server) on the localhost:8080 with the parameter id given. Using the method deleteResponseById(id) from class RequestDaoService.

        @DeleteMapping annotation is a composed annotation that acts as a shortcut for @RequestMapping(method = RequestMethod.DELETE).

        Parameters:
        id - corresponds to the identifier of 'Request' object.
        Throws:
        RequestNotFoundException - if request is null
